Mail-in-a-Box patch: lock mail server configuration in oxi webmail
======================================================================

oxi normally lets users supply their own IMAP/SMTP host, port, and TLS
settings at login time. On a MIAB box this is undesirable - the servers
are pre-configured and should not be overridable by the login request.
Allowing it would let any user of the login form point oxi at an
arbitrary mail server, bypassing the intended deployment.

This patch adds an ALLOW_CUSTOM_MAIL_SERVERS config flag (default true
for upstream compatibility) and, when set to false, enforces that:

  - Any login request that includes imap_host, imap_port, imap_tls,
    smtp_host, smtp_port, or smtp_tls is rejected with 403 FORBIDDEN.
  - All server settings are taken exclusively from server-side
    configuration. SMTP_HOST remains optional and falls back to
    IMAP_HOST when not set.
  - IMAP_HOST is required at startup in locked mode; the server refuses
    to start if it is missing.

MIAB's webmail.sh sets ALLOW_CUSTOM_MAIL_SERVERS=false in the runtime
config, so the box's own Dovecot/Postfix instances are the only targets
oxi will ever connect to.

Behavioural note - TLS default change
--------------------------------------
Upstream oxi defaulted imap_tls and smtp_tls to true when absent from
the login request. This patch changes both fields to Option<bool> so
that omitting them in custom mode inherits config.tls_enabled instead
of hardcoding true. This is intentional for MIAB (TLS_ENABLED=false
on loopback), but is a visible change for any downstream custom-mode
client that previously relied on the true default.

Files changed:
  backend/src/config.rs              - AppConfig field + default fn + tests
  backend/src/routes/auth.rs         - LoginRequest, EffectiveServerConfig,
                                       login, unit tests
  backend/src/routes/health.rs       - AppConfig literal: new field
  backend/src/routes/tests.rs        - AppConfig literals: new field
  backend/src/routes/display_preferences.rs - AppConfig literal: new field
  backend/src/main.rs                - startup validation for locked mode

To regenerate this patch against an updated oxi commit:
  git clone https://github.com/c0h1b4/oxi.git oxi
  cd oxi
  git checkout <new-commit>
  git apply ../management/oxi/1_miab_oxi_auth_patch.patch
  # resolve any conflicts, make adjustments for the new version
  git diff --no-color HEAD > ../management/oxi/1_miab_oxi_auth_patch.patch

